  "source": "[\\sum:of{m}:and{n}]\nDefines: s is \\set.theoretic.natural.number\nwhen: m, n is \\set.theoretic.natural.number\nexpresses:\n. \\sum:of{m}:and{\\set.theoretic.zero} = m\n. forAll: k is \\set.theoretic.natural.number\n  then: \\sum:of{m}:and{\\set.theoretic.successor{k}} = \\set.theoretic.successor{\\sum:of{m}:and{k}}\nDocumented:\n. called: \"sum of $m?$ and $n?$\"\n. written: \"m? + n?\"\n. description: \"The sum $m + n$, defined by recursion on $n$: $m + 0 = m$ and $m + n^+ = (m + n)^+$. Addition is the binary operation given by $+$.\"\nId: \"143db882-1e6d-4357-a241-783c6daa562c\"",
